# Overview

YANG module for management of GPIOs

Allows configuration of direction of each available GPIO and logic level
for the outputs. Allows monitoring of the current values of the inputs.


# Dependencies
Installed netconfd and yangcli
 apt-get install netconfd yangcli

# Installation
 autoreconf -i -f
 ./configure CFLAGS="-g -O0"  CXXFLAGS="-g -O0" --prefix=/usr
 make
 make install


# Testing installation

 sudo netconfd --module=lsi-gpios  --no-startup --superuser=pi

Other terminal:
 yangcli --server=localhost --user=pi --password=raspberry



...

 yangcli pi@localhost> create /gpios/gpio[name='27'] -- level=0

 yangcli pi@localhost> create /gpios/gpio[name='17']
 
 yangcli pi@localhost> commit
 
 yangcli pi@localhost> xget /gpios-state
 
 rpc-reply {
   data {
     gpios {
       gpio 17 {
         name 17
         level 0
       }
       gpio 27 {
         name 27
         level 0
       }
     }
   }
 }

# Blinking LED
We can validate the implementation with a makeshift resistor
and LED circuit connecting GPIO17, GPIO27 and GND

     R1=1K  +LED-    R2=1K
  +-|/\/\|-+-K|-+-|/\/\|-+
  |             |        |
  x             x        x
 GND          GPIO17   GPIO27
PIN#09        PIN#11   PIN#13
